## Validation

Simply MCP validates your interface definitions during dry-run to catch errors before runtime.

### Automatic Type Coercion (v4.0.0+)

Number and boolean parameters are automatically coerced from JSON-RPC strings:

```typescript
// Number parameters work correctly
interface AddTool extends ITool {
  params: { a: NumberParam; b: NumberParam };
  result: { sum: number };
}

add: AddTool = async (params) => {
  return { sum: params.a + params.b };  // 42 + 58 = 100 ‚úÖ
};
```

**Type Coercion Details:**
- Number parameters: `"42"` ‚Üí `42`
- Boolean parameters: `"true"` ‚Üí `true`
- String parameters: No coercion needed

### Parameter Validation Rules

**IMPORTANT:** Always use separate IParam interfaces. Do NOT use inline intersection types:

```typescript
// ‚ùå INCORRECT - Will fail dry-run validation
interface MyTool extends ITool {
  params: {
    count: { type: 'number'; description: '...' } & IParam;
  };
}

// ‚úÖ CORRECT - Always use separate interfaces
interface CountParam extends IParam {
  type: 'number';
  description: 'Number of items';
}

interface MyTool extends ITool {
  params: {
    count: CountParam;
  };
}
```

**Why This Matters:**
- Inline `& IParam` is NOT supported by the schema generator
- Type coercion won't be applied (numbers received as strings)
- Arithmetic operations will fail silently
- Dry-run validation catches this error early

**Running Validation:**

```bash
# Always validate before running
npx simply-mcp run server.ts --dry-run

# Success output:
# ‚úì Dry run complete
# ‚úì Tools: 3, Prompts: 1
# ‚úì Ready to run

# Error output shows fix instructions:
# ‚úó Dry run failed
# ‚ùå CRITICAL ERROR: Parameter 'count' uses inline IParam intersection.
# [Detailed fix instructions follow]
```

**Learn More:**
- üìò [Validation Guide](./docs/guides/VALIDATION.md) - Complete validation rules and troubleshooting
- üìò [API Core - Type Coercion](./docs/guides/API_CORE.md#type-coercion) - Technical details
- üìÅ **Examples**: `examples/interface-params.ts`, `examples/interface-advanced.ts`

